The paper discusses a user study on search term suggestion services for digital libraries, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL) sub-categories. The study also involves the use of vocabularies and thesaurus terms, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper focuses on user interaction and assistance, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
